449
00:27:58,175 --> 00:27:59,575
So what are you doing?

450
00:27:59,775 --> 00:28:03,175
You missed your rounds.
You didn't scrub in at the gastrectomy.

451
00:28:03,375 --> 00:28:04,675
l had to do something.

452
00:28:04,875 --> 00:28:06,275
Why don't you do your job?

453
00:28:10,475 --> 00:28:12,875
Mr. Murphy is a 35-year-old
in good health...

454
00:28:13,075 --> 00:28:16,375
...admitted for a meniscectomy.
He's scheduled for this morning.

455
00:28:16,575 --> 00:28:18,775
Promises, promises.
They keep telling me...

456
00:28:18,975 --> 00:28:20,675
...there's a delay, another half-hour.

457
00:28:20,875 --> 00:28:23,175
Well, the suspense
is really killing me.

458
00:28:23,375 --> 00:28:25,375
l thought you doctors
liked to operate.

459
00:28:25,575 --> 00:28:28,074
-We'll get to you.
-l'd hate to be left out.

460
00:28:28,274 --> 00:28:29,674
How did you get your injury?

461
00:28:30,174 --> 00:28:31,374
Playing touch football.

462
00:28:31,574 --> 00:28:34,074
You know, with the guys,
horsing around.

463
00:28:35,374 --> 00:28:37,474
<i>Dr. Wheeler, see Dr. Harris.</i>

464
00:28:37,674 --> 00:28:39,374
<i>See Dr. Harris in his office.</i>

465
00:28:39,574 --> 00:28:41,774
The chief of surgery himself.

466
00:28:42,174 --> 00:28:44,274
Playing touch football, huh?

467
00:28:44,474 --> 00:28:48,474
Yeah. So l come in,
and all that happens--

468
00:28:52,174 --> 00:28:53,774
Thanks very much, Herb.

469
00:28:53,974 --> 00:28:55,774
We'll get together on it later.

470
00:28:57,174 --> 00:28:58,174
Would you come in?

471
00:29:02,274 --> 00:29:03,574
Excuse me.

472
00:29:15,674 --> 00:29:17,374
Sit down, Sue.

473
00:29:25,474 --> 00:29:27,474
<i>It's Senator Brooke's office.</i>

474
00:29:27,674 --> 00:29:30,374
<i>He wonders if you can
change the meeting to four.</i>

475
00:29:30,574 --> 00:29:32,574
Yes, four is fine.
Notify Henry.

476
00:29:32,774 --> 00:29:33,973
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

477
00:29:42,673 --> 00:29:47,073
l like to think that Boston Memorial
is the best hospital in the city...

478
00:29:47,273 --> 00:29:49,073
...perhaps in the country.

479
00:29:49,673 --> 00:29:51,473
l'm committed to it...

480
00:29:51,873 --> 00:29:54,973
...to the house staff we have here,
and to you.

481
00:29:55,173 --> 00:29:56,873
l think you know that.

482
00:29:57,273 --> 00:30:00,073
But we have certain constraints
imposed on us.

483
00:30:00,673 --> 00:30:05,373
One is the state law concerning
privacy in computer data access.

484
00:30:06,573 --> 00:30:08,473
An unauthorized entry was made
